cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the resolution systems for quantified Boolean formulas (QBF) and Dependency QBFs (DQBF), which are related to logic.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as QBF and DQBF are important in AI for solving problems such as planning and verification.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the strengths and weaknesses of different proof systems for QBF and DQBF, which can be seen as algorithmic techniques.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with formal systems and their relation to programming languages.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as QBF and DQBF are important in complexity theory.
